# Copy to deploy/hermes-sidecar.runtime.env and point HERMES_SIDECAR_RUNTIME_ENV_FILE at it.
#
# This file is injected into the real Hermes sidecar runtime container with compose `env_file:`.
# Put runtime-specific credentials/config here.
#
# The proxy variables (HTTP_PROXY / HTTPS_PROXY / NO_PROXY) are injected by
# deploy/compose.hermes-sidecar.override.yaml, so you usually do not need
# to repeat them here unless your image expects additional custom names.
# If your real image uses app-level trust variables instead of the OS trust store,
# common examples are:
# NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS=/path/in/container/to/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
# REQUESTS_CA_BUNDLE=/path/in/container/to/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
# SSL_CERT_FILE=/path/in/container/to/combined-ca-bundle.pem

# Example placeholders only — replace with the actual variables your Hermes image expects.
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# HERMES_CONFIG_PATH=/workspace/.hermes/config.yaml
